.START 

Penn Traffic Co. said its board approved the previously announced restructuring of its investments in P&C Foods Markets Inc. and Grand Union Co. 

In exchange for its current equity investment in P&C, Penn Traffic will increase its common equity ownership in Grand Union to 40% from 24% and will receive $67 million in two classes of Grand Union preferred stock.
Penn Traffic, a supermarket and dairy concern, said the securities it receives in the transaction have an indicated value of about $89 million.
P&C will become a unit of Grand Union. 

